description: The Correctional Service Canada has a requirement to enhance support and services, as necessary, to high-risk sex offenders in order to help meet two specific corporate objectives: the safe management of eligible offenders during their transition from the institution to the community, and while under supervision; and, in the case of Indigenous offenders, effective, culturally appropriate interventions and reintegration support for First Nations, Metis and Inuit offenders.
